This paper deals with the problem of overfitting in deep neural networks for aerial image classification. It proposes a method of training neural networks to optimize image representations in the embedded space in addition to optimizing the final classification score. This is a common problem in computer vision, and specifically in image classification, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a novel approach to training neural networks, which involves optimizing image representations in the embedded space, which is a form of unsupervised learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of visualizations to analyze the performance of the neural network, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
